An essential compilation from all phases of Avril’s pioneering career as one of the 21st century’s breakout pop icons, Avril Lavigne – Greatest Hits features 20 career-spanning fan-favourites from her record-smashing catalogue including the RIAA 3x platinum-certified ‘Complicated’ and 2x platinum-certified ‘Sk8er Boi’ from her chart-topping 2002 debut album ‘Let Go’ (Artista) through her seventh studio album ‘Love Sux’ (Elektra/DTA) with songs such as ‘Bite Me’, ‘Bois Lie’ (feat. Machine Gun Kelly) and ‘I’m a Mess’ with Yungblud.

Avril Lavigne, the Canadian singer and songwriter, took the music world by storm in the early 2000s. She became internationally recognised with her debut album "Let Go" and was quickly regarded as the voice of a generation. Lavigne, who is known for her punk attitude and catchy rock-pop songs, has received numerous awards throughout her career. Her second album "Under My Skin" cemented her status as a rock icon. Away from music, Lavigne has also appeared in various film and television projects and established herself as a businesswoman. Her unmistakable voice and her ability to evolve musically have secured her a loyal fan base. With "The Greatest Hits Tour", Lavigne celebrates not only two decades in the music business, but also the enduring connection with her fans.
